 :tx/rationale "Create task: EPIC: R(t) Feedback Loop — Learn routing weights from agent follow-through behavior (INV-GUIDANCE-010, INV-GUIDANCE-005, ADR-TOPOLOGY-004). BACKGROUND: The single highest-leverage non-obvious addition. R(t) routing currently uses hardcoded weights [0.25, 0.25, 0.20, 0.15, 0.10, 0.05] for its 6 features (pagerank, betweenness, critical_path, blocker_ratio, staleness, priority_boost). These weights are theoretical — they've never been validated against actual agent behavior. THE INSIGHT: Every ACP projection is a PREDICTION ('you should do X'). The agent's next command is GROUND TRUTH. The gap between prediction and action is a LEARNING SIGNAL. By tracking which recommendations agents follow (follow-through rate per feature), we can empirically optimize the weights. This is the PGO (Profile-Guided Optimization) pattern from topology (ADR-TOPOLOGY-004) applied to guidance routing. It's also the significance accumulation from SEED.md §7 applied to output quality. WHY THIS COMPOUNDS: Each session generates ~20-50 action-outcome pairs. After 10 sessions: 200-500 data points. The routing gets empirically better every session. WHY THIS IS DEFENSIBLE: The behavioral data is project-specific — no other system has YOUR project's agent behavior history. The weights become a learned competitive advantage. SUBSUMES: Part of t-241cf210 (PGO pattern), extends t-b764 (significance tracking). TRACES TO: INV-GUIDANCE-010, INV-GUIDANCE-005, ADR-TOPOLOGY-004 (PGO), SEED.md §7 (self-improvement loop)."
